d from the XXL selection function modelling. We\nalso considered a further seven optically-selected cluster candidates\nassociated with faint XXL sources that were not classed as clusters. By\ndecontaminating and vetting these distant clusters, we provide a pure sample of\nclusters at redshift z $>$ 1 for deeper follow-up observations, and demonstrate\nthe utility of using Chandra snapshots to test for AGN in surveys with high\nsensitivity but poor angular resolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Aug 2018 10:54:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-21"}
